TEXT.0: This file contains numerical moments computed from measurements of the

TEXT.1: Los Alamos Magnetospheric Plasma Analyzer (MPA) [Bame et al.,

TEXT.3: The moments are presented in s/c coordinates: the z-axis is aligned with

TEXT.4: the spin axis, which points radially toward the center of the Earth;

TEXT.5: the x-axis is in the plane containing the spacecraft spin axis and the spin

TEXT.6: axis of the Earth, with +X generally northward; and the y-axis points

TEXT.7: generally eastward. Polar angles are measured relative to the spin axis

TEXT.8: (+Z), and azimuthal angles are measured around the z-axis, with zero along

TEXT.9: the +X direction. The moments are computed for three 'species':

TEXT.11: alle (electrons, ~30eV - ~45keV ). The electron measurements are obtained

TEXT.12: 21.5 secs after the ion measurements. Epoch is the measurement time

TEXT.13: appropriate for the ions. The moments are computed after the fluxes are

TEXT.14: corrected for background and s/c potential. Algorithms for these corrections

TEXT.15: are relatively unsophisticated, so the moments are suspect during times of

TEXT.16: high background and/or high spacecraft potential. Because the determined

TEXT.17: spacecraft potential is not very precise, the magnitude of the low-energy

TEXT.18: ion flow velocity is probably not accurate, but the flow direction is well

TEXT.19: determined.  Tperp and Tpara are obtained from diagonalization of the

TEXT.20: 3-dimensional temperature matrix, with the parallel direction assigned

TEXT.21: to the eigenvalue which is most different from the other two.

TEXT.22: The corresponding eigenvector is the symmetry axis of the distribution and

TEXT.23: should be equivalent to the magnetic field direction. The eigenvalue ratio

TEXT.24: Tperp/Tmid, which is provided for each species, is a measure of the symmetry

TEXT.25: of the distribution and should be ~1.0 for a good determination. Several of

TEXT.26: the parameters have a fairly high daily dynamic range and for survey purposes

TEXT.27: are best displayed logarithmically. These parameters are indicated by

TEXT.28: non-zero 'SCALEMIN' values in this file. A quality flag value of 1

TEXT.29: indicates that the values are  preliminary and have not been checked
